4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE MONTANA END OF WATCH
5 TRUST; REQUIRING APPLICATIONS FOR PAYMENTS FROM THE END OF WATCH TRUST DUE TO
6 CATASTROPHIC INJURY TO INCLUDE A WORKERS' COMPENSATION DETERMINATION OF
7 PERMANENT AND TOTAL DISABILITY; ALLOWING LEGAL CHILDREN OF AN OFFICER TO RECEIVE
8 PAYMENTS AFTER THEY TURN 18 IN CERTAIN CIRCUMSTANCES; PROVIDING RULEMAKING
9 AUTHORITY TO THE DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE; REVISING DEFINITIONS; AND AMENDING SECTIONS
10 2-15-2040, 2-15-2041, 2-15-2042, 2-15-2043, 2-15-2044, AND 2-15-2045, MCA.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Administration by department of justice -- rulemaking authority. (1)
15 The department of justice may assess a fee not to exceed 15% of the amount appropriated to the department
16 for the purposes of administrating the end of watch trust fund.
17 (2) The department may adopt rules for the purposes of executing its obligations under 2-15-2040
18 through 2-15-2045 and [section 2]. This includes rules that create:
19 (a) a process for distributing payments to applicants approved by the board;
20 (b) a process through which the board approves or denies applications for payments distributed in
21 accordance with this section;
22 (c) guidelines for appeal of board decisions;
23 (d) information security and document retention policies;
24 (e) board training requirements; and
25 (f) reporting requirements.
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Determination of eligibility -- board approval -- appeals. (1) A law
28 enforcement officer or the officer's immediate family is eligible for payment from the end of watch trust after the
