7 Section 3. Section 2-15-2040, MCA, is amended to read:
8 "2-15-2040. Definitions. For the purposes of 2-15-2040 through 2-15-2045 and [sections 1 and 2],
9 the following definitions apply:
10 (1) "Board" means the Montana end of watch trust board established in 2-15-2044.
11 (2) "Catastrophic injury" means an injury directly related to an individual's required employment
12 duties with direct or proximate consequences that renders the individual in need of 24-hour care continuous
13 care to complete basic activities of daily living, permanently incapacitates the individual, and permanently
14 prevents the individual from performing any gainful form of work, and results in a determination of permanent
15 and total disability, as that term is defined in 39-71-116, at the time of maximum medical improvement.
16 (3) "Department" means the department of justice.
17 (4) "Immediate family" means a law enforcement officer's spouse and legal dependent children
18 under age 18 years of age, including children to whom the law enforcement officer is a legal guardian.
19 (5) "In the line of duty" means as the direct result of an action taken by a law enforcement officer or
20 an activity in which a law enforcement officer participated:
21 (a) as required or authorized by law, rule, regulation, condition of employment, or professional
22 ethics; and
23 (b) in the course and scope of carrying out the law enforcement officer's sworn obligations; or
24 (b) (c) for which compensation is provided by the officer's employer or would have been provided by
25 the officer's employer if the officer had been on duty at the time the action in question was taken.
26 (6) "Law enforcement officer" means:
27 (a) a police officer, deputy sheriff, undersheriff, highway patrol officer, investigator appointed by
28 the department of justice, fish and game warden, park ranger, or other public safety officer with arrest authority,
